# Std ‚Äî Selective and Either

Exercises `Either`, the `Selective` typeclass on `List` / `Option`,
and the branching helpers.

[Left, Right, mapRight, flatMapRight, foldEither, isLeft, isRight](../std/either.ssc)

[listSelective, optionSelective, selectList, selectOption, branchList, branchOption](../std/selective.ssc)

## Either basics

```scalascript
val r: Either[String, Int] = Right(42)
val l: Either[String, Int] = Left("nope")

println(mapRight(r, (x: Int) => x + 1))
println(mapRight(l, (x: Int) => x + 1))
val blocked: Either[String, Int] = Left("blocked")
println(flatMapRight(r, (x: Int) => Right(x * 2)))
println(flatMapRight(r, (x: Int) => blocked))
println(foldEither(r, (s: String) => "got " + s, (n: Int) => "ok " + n))
println(foldEither(l, (s: String) => "got " + s, (n: Int) => "ok " + n))
println(isLeft(l))
println(isRight(r))
```

## Selective ‚Äî `select`

```scalascript
val recover = (s: String) => s.length
println(selectList(List(Right(10), Left("ab"), Right(99)), List(recover)))

val someRight: Option[Either[String, Int]] = Some(Right(10))
val someLeft:  Option[Either[String, Int]] = Some(Left("hello"))
val noRecover: Option[String => Int]       = None
println(selectOption(someRight, Some(recover)))
println(selectOption(someLeft,  Some(recover)))
println(selectOption(someLeft,  noRecover))
```

## Branching ‚Äî `branch`

```scalascript
val onErr = (s: String) => "err:" + s
val onOk  = (n: Int)    => "ok:"  + n
println(branchList(List(Right(1), Left("bad"), Right(2)), List(onErr), List(onOk)))

val r2: Option[Either[String, Int]] = Some(Right(7))
val l2: Option[Either[String, Int]] = Some(Left("oops"))
println(branchOption(r2, Some(onErr), Some(onOk)))
println(branchOption(l2, Some(onErr), Some(onOk)))
```
